<section
	id="ratype_events">

	<title>Events</title>

	<para>The
		Events fired by &THIS.RA;
		Resource Adaptor represent changes in call or connection.
	</para>
	<para>
		Events fired on
		<literal>NetworkConnection</literal>
		Activity

		has following:
	</para>
	<variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
			<term>class</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>javax.media.mscontrol.networkconnection.SdpPortManagerEvent</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term>vendor</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>org.mobicents</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term>version</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>1.0</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term>name prefix</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>javax.media.mscontrol.networkconnection.SdpPortManagerEvent.</para>
				<para>Note that this is name prefix. Full event name is concatenation of this prefix and name listed in table below.</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
	</variablelist>

	<table
		frame="all"
		pgwide="1">
		<title>
			Events fired on the
			<literal>NetworkConnection</literal>
			Activity
		</title>
		<tgroup
			colsep="1"
			cols="2"
			align="left">
			<colspec
				colnum="1"
				colname="c0" />
			<colspec
				colnum="2"
				colname="c1" />


			<thead>
				<row>
					<entry>Name</entry>
					<entry>Description</entry>
				</row>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<row>
					<entry>ANSWER_GENERATED</entry>
					<entry>Generated when media server returns <literal>SDP</literal>. This <literal>SDP</literal> is answer to one present in client request, ie. in <literal>SIP INVITE</literal> </entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>ANSWER_PROCESSED</entry>
					<entry>Generated when media server is processing <literal>SDP</literal> offer.</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>NETWORK_STREAM_FAILURE</entry>
					<entry>Generated on failure in media server. <literal>SDP</literal> present indicates remaining available streams.</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>OFFER_GENERATED</entry>
					<entry>Generated when media server returns <literal>SDP</literal> offer. </entry>
				</row>
			</tbody>
		</tgroup>
	</table>
	
	<para>
		Events fired on
		<literal>MediaGroup</literal>
		Activity
		has following:
	</para>
	<variablelist>
		
		<varlistentry>
			<term>vendor</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>org.mobicents</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term>version</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>1.0</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		
	</variablelist>
	
	
	<table frame="all" pgwide="1">
			<title>Events fired on the <literal>MediaGroup</literal> Activity</title>
			<tgroup colsep="1" cols="3">
				<colspec colnum="1" colname="c0" colwidth="2*"/>
				<colspec colnum="2" colname="c1" colwidth="2*"/>
				<colspec colnum="3" colname="c2" colwidth="1*"/>

			<thead>
				<row>
					<entry>Name</entry>
					<entry>Event Class</entry>
					<entry>Description</entry>
				</row>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<row>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol. 
					join.JoinEvent 
					.JOINED</entry>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol. 
					join.JoinEvent</entry>					
					<entry>Generated when resources are joined, ie. <literal>MediaGroup</literal> and <literal>NetworkConnection</literal></entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol. 
					join.JoinEvent.
					 UNJOINED</entry>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol. 
					join.JoinEvent</entry>			
					<entry>Generated when resource are disconnected.</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEvent 
					.PLAY_COMPLETED</entry>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEven</entry>					
					<entry>Generated when player finishes its task.</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEvent 
					.PAUSED</entry>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEven</entry>					
					<entry>Generated when player ceases media stream.</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEvent 
					.RESUMED</entry>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEven</entry>					
					<entry>Generated when player starts playback from moment it paused previously.</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEvent 
					.SPEED_CHANGED</entry>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEven</entry>					
					<entry>Generated when speed of playback changes.</entry>
				</row>
				<row>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEvent 
					.VOLUME_CHANGED</entry>
					<entry>javax.media 
					.mscontrol.mediagroup. 
					PlayerEven</entry>						
					<entry>Generated when volume of playback changes.</entry>
				</row>
				
			</tbody>
		</tgroup>
	</table>
	<important>
		<para>
			Spaces where introduced in
			<literal>Name</literal>
			,
			<literal>Vendor</literal>
			and
			<literal>Event Class</literal>
			column values, to correctly render the table. Please remove them when using copy/paste.
		</para>
	</important>
	<important>
		<para>More details for each event type may be obtained on the javadocs of each event type class.</para>
	</important>
</section>